OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1780567570
OL,3,CTATA Steel workers jailed after tin
OL,4,Cworth #1.2m stolen from site
OL,6,FThree TATA Steel employees who
OL,7,Fconspired with an outside man to steal
OL,8,Ftin ingots worth nearly #1.2m have
OL,9,Fbeen sentenced at Swansea Crown Court.
OL,11,FThomas Ashford, 35, Richard Jones, 29,
OL,12,Fand Stewart Jones, 56 all worked at
OL,13,Fthe TATA steelworks in Trostre,
OL,14,FLlanelli.
OL,16,FThe men facilitated access to the site
OL,17,Ffor Matthew Membury, 32, on multiple
OL,18,Foccasions, and assisted him with the
OL,19,Fremoval of tin ingots.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/14
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,467,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1780567570
OL,3,CTATA Steel workers jailed after tin
OL,4,Cworth #1.2m stolen from site
OL,6,FThe ingots were then melted down and
OL,7,Fsold to scrap merchants.
OL,9,FIn a sentencing hearing at Swansea
OL,10,FCrown Court today (Tuesday, June 2)
OL,11,Fthe prosecution described the case as
OL,12,Fa "persistent and sophisticated
OL,13,Fconspiracy" which amounted to a "gross
OL,14,Fbreach of trust" and was "well co-
OL,15,Fordinated" by the men.
OL,17,FThe court heard that the case involved
OL,18,Fthe theft of multiple one tonne tin
OL,19,Fbundles of ingots which were then sold
OL,20,Fto metal dealers with pre-agreed
OL,21,Fshares between the defendants.
OL,26,@uD@KO]
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/14
